              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Target was thick plate of Yb-10mm*10mm*1mm. In Yb",
                "plate a deuteron beam was implanted at E(d) =6.45 keV",
                "for a long time until proton yield became almost",
                "constant. A liquid nitrogen trap was set at the",
                "scattering chamber and no carbon build-up on the target",
                "was observed."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COMP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The thick target yield of the reaction in Ti",
                "metal with the calculated value for bare cross  section",
                "is presented.",
                "The electron screening potential for the target is",
                "obtained as 81 +/- 10 eV.  Systematical errors of the",
                "deduced screening potential in Yb are considered to be",
                "+25/-35 eV, due to the uncertainty of the stopping",
                "power and +13-eV due to uncertainty of the number of",
                "the deuterons in metal during the bombardment."
              ]
            }
